rComments: Slides are brief and she talks quietly. Her transition between concepts was vague and lectures are not very interactive, but she's approachable for content-related clarification so ask! The lecture material is simple but picky grading. The textbook is ambiguous (since the field is new), but focus reading on lecture-concepts and you'd be on-track.

If you want to take a course that expects so much from you on the test but teaches you NOTHING, this is the course for you! Honestly, worse course I ever took. The prof doesn't teach you anything, her slides suck, they make no sense. The only good thing about this course was the TA.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: Only the first row of students can hear her. She speaks at an incredibly low volume and even with a mic you can hardly hear. She is so monotone that you cant stay awake in class, I wasnt the only one with this problem. Overall, she is very socially awkward so I dont think this helps with being a professor. She is difficult to understand over all
